At the census of 2020, there were 337 residents of West Falls.  Of these, 316 ({{percentage|319|337|2}}) were white alone, 1 ({{percentage|1|337|2}}) was Native Hawaiian and Pacific Islander, 2 ({{percentage|2|337|2}}) were of other races, and 18 ({{percentage|18|337|2}}) were of two or more races.<ref>[https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALPL2020.P1?t=Populations%20and%20People&g=160XX00US4282952 2020 Census data | P1 RACE for West Falls CDP, Pennsylvania]</ref>

As of the 2022 American Community Survey, the CDP had 159 households of which 84 ({{percentage|84|139|2}}) had married couples living in them, 21 of which ({{percentage|21|139|2}}) had a married couple with a child under age 18 living with them.  The average household size was 1.94 and the average family size was 2.49.<ref>[https://data.census.gov/table?t=Families%20and%20Living%20Arrangements&g=160XX00US4282952 2022 American Community Survey Data | DP02 Selected Social Characteristics for West Falls CDP, Pennsylvania]</ref>
